CalculateField AddressPoints Name "RAPID RIVER RUN" VB #
CalculateField AddressPoints POCOname "RAPID RIVER RUN" VB #
CalculateField AddressPoints FullName "[HouseNumber] & " " & trim([PreType]) & " " & trim([Name]) & " " & trim([Type])" VB #
CalculateField AddressPoints FullName "[HouseNumber] & " " & trim([PreType]) & " " & trim([POCOname]) & " " & trim([Type])" VB #

dataExt.exDesc: [Addresses are added as we become aware of them. Only current addresses are kept.]

dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[This is a point representation of building addresses designed for reference and geo-locating.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This point data layer represents buildings for Portage County, Wisconsin at year-end 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Portage_Buildings_YE2016. [This file contains point data representing buildings placed based upon aerial photography. The points are attributed with address information with both County names and 911 ani/ali verified names. The points are also attributed with emergency service numbers and municipality.]

dataIdInfo.suppInfo:
Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements.
This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.
